description: Barry Turner discovers whodunnit in the best Classic Crime novels out this month.
title: Classic Crime to keep you guessing: Murder At The Allotment by Julie Wassmer, Agatha Christie's Marple by Mark Aldridge and The Christmas Guest by Peter Swanson

description: Claud Cockburn saw it all. As Peter Hitchens finds out in this new biography, he was a communist, industry influencing journalist, and the real life Sally Bowles's lover.
title: Claud Cockburn: Champagne Communist, Sally Bowles's lover… and British spy?

description: Affleck, 52, was reportedly unaware that Lopez was planning to speak out when she did but is aware that given her history of documenting their romance she could talk about their split 'forever.'
title: Why Ben Affleck feels he can't 'get away' from Jennifer Lopez after she breaks silence on their divorce

description: Tom Brady has given fans a tour of his trophy cabinet, and the extremely impressive space features mementos from Cristiano Ronaldo, Floyd Mayweather and Novak Djokovic.
title: Inside Tom Brady's trophy cabinet as the legendary QB shares mementos from Cristiano Ronaldo, Floyd Mayweather and more

description: With 25 days to go until the United States chooses a new ­President, the race looks as close as it could be. The ­election once again looks set to be decided by a few thousand voters.
title: LORD ASHCROFT: The swing state that offers vital clues to which candidate will win this closest of US elections

description: A new mum was furious when she thought her husband stole her orange juice - the only drink she could consume postpartum - but the truth was much more sinister.
title: I flew into a rage when I thought my husband stole my orange juice - then we checked the security cameras and spotted the real thief

description:
They tend to gather after drop-off and I like to have an excuse ready so I can make a quick exit.
Sometimes, however, it's unavoidable and I don't want to appear standoffish.
title: Hell of being a helicopter daughter: My elderly mother needs constant attention - and we BOTH resent it

description: JEFF POWELL MBE: His disillusion with the split decision gleaned by Sugar Ray Leonard was so profound that he turned his back on boxing and moved to a land where he didn't speak the language.
title: BOXING'S FOUR KINGS - Part Three: JEFF POWELL MBE on the most controversial fight of all as he reveals why Marvin Hagler was still so stung by Sugar Ray Leonard a decade later

description: Snuggling in for a cuddle at bedtime, seven-year-old Laurie Lloyd-Wilson whispers words that make his mother Josie's heart ache. 'I miss Daddy,' he says.
title: How I gave birth to my husband's children... after he died

description: The five-day festival takes place at Somerset's Worth Farm and draws in around around 200,000 music fans each year to watch some of the world's biggest musicians perform.
title: Glastonbury 2025 ticket sale date and prices REVEALED- with huge pop stars rumoured to be headlining

description: As I danced at my silver wedding anniversary party this summer, I couldn't have been happier. I was in the arms of the man of my dreams, feeling my usual spark of excitement.

description: My husband and I have a secret that we like to keep ­hidden from public view. It's not that we're swingers or Morris dancers, but we don't sleep together. Not in the same bed, anyway.

description: When I read a report, this week claiming that there are 745,000 illegal immigrants living in Britain, my immediate reaction was: Is that all?

description: HUGH OSMOND: Oddly enough, I sympathise with the Prime Minister. Sue Gray's demise speaks to the fundamental truth that, in business, it's easy to get hiring decisions wrong.
title: HUGH OSMOND: No wonder businesses are running scared at anti-growth policies

description: Her romance with Connell in TV drama Normal People caused a global sensation - and now actress Daisy Edgar-Jones is set to take on probably the greatest role in romantic fiction.
title: ALISON BOSHOFF: Actress Daisy Edgar-Jones to take on probably the greatest role in romantic fiction as Elizabeth Bennet in Jane Austen's Pride And Prejudice

description: TOM UTLEY: Don't tell my sons, but a sure way to increase my suffering and hasten my departure from this world would be to play me Frank Sinatra's version of My Way, on a loop.
title: TOM UTLEY: Don't even try to play My Way as I lie on my deathbed. I don't want to add murder to my list of deadly sins...
